Description: Fragment of handle from a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine red-brown; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.28, 14. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0392.43.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0396)
